-- Barwa Gets $3.5 Billion Islamic Financing for Projects From Qatari Diar
-- Shaji Mathew
-- 2010-07-22T06:52:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/barwa-gets-3-5-billion-islamic-financing-for-projects-from-qatari-diar.html

          
          
             Barwa Real Estate Co., a Qatar-based
property developer, said one of its units got a $3.5 billion
Islamic murabaha financing from Qatari Diar Finance.  
 The financing for Barwa City Real Estate Co. is in two
murabaha contracts: the first provides $1 billion maturing in
July 2015, and the second $2.5 billion due July 2020, Barwa said
in a statement to the Qatar bourse today. Qatari Diar Finance is
a unit of Qatari Diar Real Estate Investment Co.  
 Barwaâ€™s agreement with Qatari Diar will allow for financing
of Barwa Financial District WLL and Barwa Commercial Avenue Co.,
according to a statement.  
